15:56.930 --> 15:59.459
And maybe if you took
out all of those maybes,

15:59.484 --> 16:01.178
that's exactly what I did.

16:01.203 --> 16:03.077
So I was a bargaining chip?

16:03.102 --> 16:04.147
I'm sorry, Zoey.

16:04.172 --> 16:06.498
But, if you visit her with me,

16:06.523 --> 16:08.311
I will give you anything you want.

16:08.336 --> 16:10.772
Flat-screen TV? Ferrari?

16:10.944 --> 16:13.869
I'm lying, I can really only
afford a medium fro-yo.

16:13.894 --> 16:16.027
Mm.

16:20.725 --> 16:22.725
Then let's go to college.

16:23.296 --> 16:26.044
We're looking for Sather Gate,
Sather Hall or Sather comments.

16:26.069 --> 16:28.843
Who is this Sather guy,
and exactly how rich was he?

16:29.006 --> 16:30.309
Whoop! Incoming.

16:30.334 --> 16:32.786
Whoa. Nice reflexes.

16:33.077 --> 16:34.661
Did you play ultimate in college?

16:34.686 --> 16:37.739
No, I played duck the
shrapnel in Afghanistan.

16:37.764 --> 16:38.876
Did you really?

16:38.900 --> 16:41.123
I was a field medic, three tours.

16:41.403 --> 16:42.584
Wow.

16:43.335 --> 16:44.934
- You must have seen...
- Some stuff?

16:44.959 --> 16:46.661
Yeah, you could say that.

16:46.686 --> 16:48.185
How do you go through all that suffering

16:48.209 --> 16:51.380
and not let it break you?

16:51.405 --> 16:53.557
You're always so positive and...

16:53.581 --> 16:56.894
Joyful, even when things are
pretty bleak with my dad.

16:56.918 --> 16:58.462
Your dad's one of the lucky ones.

16:58.486 --> 17:01.411
He's had an awesome life, you know,

17:01.436 --> 17:04.300
with a happy home,
a family who's crazy about him.

17:04.325 --> 17:05.835
I lost friends who weren't old enough

17:05.859 --> 17:08.551
to sip their first beer...
Well, legally at least.

17:08.577 --> 17:11.474
Yeah, I get that.
It's just hard to maintain perspective

17:11.499 --> 17:13.983
when you're living with
someone dying every day.

17:14.233 --> 17:18.194
One of the reasons I
love caregiving so much

17:18.219 --> 17:22.886
is it shows me what an
insane gift all of this is,

17:22.911 --> 17:26.257
just walking around on our own
two feet, you know,

17:26.281 --> 17:30.709
making our own choices,
breathing our own breaths.

17:35.190 --> 17:36.667
Are you getting a whiff of that?

17:36.691 --> 17:38.569
Sweet, sweet Kush.

17:38.593 --> 17:41.160
Maybe I should've
gone to college instead.

17:43.584 --> 17:45.420
- You are bad.
- You can try to twist her arm.

17:45.445 --> 17:48.045
- One ounce, she's...
- I never do anything without you.

17:48.725 --> 17:50.680
- Here you are, darlings.
- Thank you.

17:50.705 --> 17:52.194
Gosh, I really love the vibe in here.

17:52.219 --> 17:54.284
- How would you describe it?
- "Lady and the Tramp"

17:54.309 --> 17:56.677
meets Lady Bird Johnson
meets "Lady Marmalade."

17:56.702 --> 17:58.389
I love that video. I used to know

17:58.413 --> 17:59.929
all the choreography when I was younger.

17:59.953 --> 18:01.084
Is that going to be the song

18:01.109 --> 18:02.753
for the first dance at your wedding?

18:02.778 --> 18:06.108
Because you should probably save
those moves for the honeymoon.

18:08.113 --> 18:10.661
Speaking of your big day, when is it?

18:10.686 --> 18:12.368
We haven't gotten our save-the-date yet.

18:12.393 --> 18:15.497
- Oh, well, it...
- We are not sure yet.

18:15.522 --> 18:16.874
Still trying to find a-a venue.

18:16.898 --> 18:19.450
Dates, really lock it in.

18:19.475 --> 18:21.078
But it would be helpful
in terms of planning

18:21.102 --> 18:22.780
to just make a decision already.

18:23.053 --> 18:24.927
Still so much to figure out.

18:24.952 --> 18:26.705
Mm-hmm. Definitely.

18:26.730 --> 18:28.430
Gotta do that.

18:30.186 --> 18:32.006
All right, does anyone
need any help in the kitchen?

18:32.030 --> 18:34.177
- Mm-mm.
- Uh, no, we got it.

18:34.202 --> 18:36.560
Come on, Jess.
Let's go check on the quiche,

18:36.584 --> 18:39.708
which is really just code for
"I need another mimosa."

18:40.898 --> 18:42.559
Do you remember that time when...

18:42.584 --> 18:44.302
What in the hell are you doing?

18:44.327 --> 18:45.770
- What do you mean?
- Don't play games.

18:45.794 --> 18:46.898
You've done enough of that with Zoey.

18:46.922 --> 18:48.803
She told me you two kissed.

18:48.828 --> 18:50.452
- She told you that?
- Of course she did.

18:50.477 --> 18:53.522
We're joined at the hip.
Now, move. Now. Go. Uh...

18:56.108 --> 18:58.473
It just happened.

18:58.498 --> 19:00.084
You have been having an emotional affair

19:00.108 --> 19:01.747
with this girl for months now,

19:01.772 --> 19:03.716
texting her, leaning on her,

19:03.741 --> 19:05.755
showing up to her
apartment late at night.

19:05.780 --> 19:07.210
- Whoa...
- And whatever it is you think

19:07.234 --> 19:09.926
you are doing to her and that
beautiful bride-to-be of yours

19:09.951 --> 19:12.022
in the next room is unacceptable.

19:12.164 --> 19:13.625
You're right, Mo.

19:14.179 --> 19:16.039
It's just, Zoey and I connect

19:16.074 --> 19:20.797
on this very deep level,
many levels actually,

19:20.822 --> 19:23.133
and there's a lot of
emotions tied up in that,

19:23.158 --> 19:24.556
many of which I don't want to go into,

19:24.580 --> 19:26.102
because it makes feel like a bad person,

19:26.126 --> 19:28.047
which I'm not, Mo.

19:29.070 --> 19:31.875
If I was, I would not care
about the feelings

19:31.900 --> 19:33.726
of that incredible woman in there

19:34.344 --> 19:37.687
who has tried very hard

19:37.712 --> 19:39.890
to help me through a very tough time.

19:40.114 --> 19:41.796
It's just...

19:44.320 --> 19:46.390
I don't know what to do...

19:47.602 --> 19:50.080
and it's tearing me up inside.

19:50.667 --> 19:52.588
I-I can't eat, I can't sleep,
and I never meant

19:52.613 --> 19:54.655
- to hurt anybody. It...
- Hey.

19:55.599 --> 20:00.580
I understand,
but hurt people hurt people,

20:00.605 --> 20:04.073
and you really need to figure this out.

20:27.394 --> 20:29.594
Welcome to the sixth floor, Maxwell.

20:30.065 --> 20:31.442
Thank you.

20:31.467 --> 20:33.687
Uh, but I'm...
You could just call me Max.

20:33.712 --> 20:35.734
I don't do nicknames.

20:36.027 --> 20:37.898
Quite the upgrade up here,
don't you think?

20:37.923 --> 20:41.169
Yeah, it's just like
the fourth floor, only more...

20:41.194 --> 20:42.939
- ... terrifying?
- That's by design,

20:42.964 --> 20:46.094
but I'm thinking it might be
time for a mood change up here.

20:46.119 --> 20:47.555
Everyone was very impressed

20:47.580 --> 20:50.062
by your participation in
The Chirp presentation.

20:50.087 --> 20:52.086
Oh, yeah. Well,
I was just kinda winging it.

20:52.111 --> 20:53.352
Well, your off-the-cuff attitude

20:53.376 --> 20:55.754
and bold creative vision are
exactly what we're missing.

20:55.779 --> 20:57.414
Sure, my team is good,

20:57.439 --> 21:00.812
but they lack your
specific right-brain flair.

21:00.837 --> 21:02.914
You designed the escape
room at the holiday party

21:02.939 --> 21:04.250
that no one could get out of.

21:04.275 --> 21:06.578
Franklin Yang had a nervous breakdown.

21:06.603 --> 21:08.242
Oh, yeah. He got fired that day.

21:08.267 --> 21:10.437
I think the escape room just
kinda put it over the top.

21:10.462 --> 21:12.906
Either way, I'd like to offer you

21:12.931 --> 21:15.601
the chance to manage your own team.

21:15.958 --> 21:17.430
I'm sorry.

21:18.243 --> 21:19.287
You want me?

21:19.312 --> 21:21.875
I want you to come up
here and shake things up.

21:21.900 --> 21:24.930
I want you to bring
your joy and your spirit

21:24.955 --> 21:28.406
and help me bring out
everyone's individual flair.

21:28.431 --> 21:31.250
Well, I'm very flattered

21:31.275 --> 21:33.469
that you think I could
do all those things,

21:33.494 --> 21:36.706
but I hadn't really
planned on making a move.

21:36.731 --> 21:39.744
I mean, uh, things are pretty
fine for me on the fourth floor.

21:39.769 --> 21:41.156
Are they?

21:41.824 --> 21:44.711
Or are you stuck treading water,

21:44.736 --> 21:47.367
waiting for something to
happen that maybe never will?

21:48.753 --> 21:50.390
Can I think about this?

21:50.415 --> 21:52.773
My offer is good for 72 hours.

21:52.798 --> 21:54.632
The clock starts now.

21:56.504 --> 21:58.416
Wow, it's so quiet.

21:58.441 --> 22:00.031
It's like the library,

22:00.056 --> 22:02.711
that I did not spend all
of my time in in college.

22:02.736 --> 22:05.234
Yeah, you're not gonna hear
a lot of talking in here.

22:05.259 --> 22:07.793
- How come?
- Because this is a deaf dorm.

22:14.908 --> 22:16.609
There she is.

22:17.044 --> 22:18.763
That's Abigail.

22:21.179 --> 22:23.804
- I don't speak sign language.
- No, it's okay.

22:23.829 --> 22:26.140
She can read lips, and I'll translate.

22:26.165 --> 22:27.663
Okay.

22:33.732 --> 22:35.397
Hey, Abby.

22:35.422 --> 22:37.116
It's been a while.

22:37.188 --> 22:39.374
I'm very happy to see you.

22:39.399 --> 22:43.561
Um, this is the famous
Zoey I texted you about.

22:43.586 --> 22:46.031
Hi. Nice shirt.

22:46.306 --> 22:49.585
I have a print of Ada Lovelace
hanging in my apartment.

22:49.938 --> 22:54.030
FYI, Ada was an
18th-century mathematician

22:54.055 --> 22:58.085
who is considered to be
one of the first coders.

22:58.110 --> 23:00.124
Love me some Lovelace.

23:00.587 --> 23:02.241
Same.

23:03.146 --> 23:06.202
Uh, it's very cool that
you work at Sprq Point.

23:06.227 --> 23:08.772
Have you thought about applying
to our internship program?

23:09.679 --> 23:11.444
I would love to

23:11.469 --> 23:13.647
once I'm back from Kenya.

23:13.672 --> 23:14.815
Amazing.

23:14.840 --> 23:16.084
What are you doing in Kenya?

23:16.109 --> 23:17.577
Wait. Kenya?

23:17.602 --> 23:20.834
Didn't we decide that you weren't
gonna go on that trip?

23:22.960 --> 23:25.733
I don't care if you got
a grant to pay for it.

23:27.344 --> 23:29.912
I'm setting up computers
at a school there,

23:29.937 --> 23:31.615
getting kids excited about STEM.

23:31.640 --> 23:34.694
I built a piece of software
that teaches them sign language

23:34.719 --> 23:35.889
while they learn English.

23:35.914 --> 23:37.162
That's so great,

23:37.187 --> 23:38.975
and it'll be amazing for your résumé,

23:39.000 --> 23:41.076
which you should definitely send me.

23:41.740 --> 23:44.498
Why would you hide this from me?

23:44.523 --> 23:46.787
How are you gonna get around Kenya?

23:46.812 --> 23:49.295
It's too risky for someone like you,

23:49.320 --> 23:51.022
and you're not going.

25:44.207 --> 25:46.218
I know you're angry.

25:46.500 --> 25:48.389
It's just...

25:53.017 --> 25:55.475
Do you need me to
translate that for you?

25:56.153 --> 25:58.873
Pretty sure I got the gist.

26:10.155 --> 26:12.005
Whoa, what's all this?

26:12.030 --> 26:14.641
Creative inspiration or
massive cry for help?

26:14.665 --> 26:16.643
These were organized by year,

26:16.667 --> 26:18.812
but I think I want to
organize them by color.

26:18.836 --> 26:21.936
Or should I go crazy
and do it by alphabet?

26:22.365 --> 26:24.239
Uh, no, I think
I'm gonna do it by color.

26:24.264 --> 26:25.986
Ooh. Do you want some tea?
I'm gonna get some tea.

26:26.010 --> 26:28.936
Oh, and banana bread.
Eddie made it. It's delicious.

26:28.961 --> 26:31.491
For your brunch? How was it?

26:31.516 --> 26:33.579
Did you talk to Simon?

26:33.604 --> 26:35.373
Read him the riot act?

26:35.903 --> 26:38.020
Chamomile or Earl Grey? You know what?

26:38.045 --> 26:39.265
You look like an Earl Grey kind of girl,

26:39.289 --> 26:41.529
so I'm gonna run to the store
and get you some real fast.

26:42.092 --> 26:43.736
Why are you running away from me?

26:43.761 --> 26:45.655
I think it's best if
you don't look at me

26:45.680 --> 26:48.255
or worry about and focus on
what I'm thinking or feeling.

26:48.280 --> 26:49.680
Uh-oh.

26:51.035 --> 26:52.280
Was it that bad?

26:52.305 --> 26:53.983
Not bad. I just told him

26:54.008 --> 26:57.570
that I didn't approve of his actions,
and he just, uh...

26:57.595 --> 26:59.100
He what?

26:59.295 --> 27:00.731
Listen, the truth is...

27:03.614 --> 27:07.247
♪ Love can be a many-splendored thing ♪

27:07.272 --> 27:11.045
♪ Can't deny the joy it brings ♪

27:11.089 --> 27:14.700
♪ A dozen roses, diamond rings ♪

27:14.725 --> 27:18.939
♪ Dreams for sale and fairy tales ♪

27:18.963 --> 27:22.709
♪ It'll make you hear a symphony ♪

27:22.733 --> 27:26.947
♪ And you just want the world to see ♪

27:26.971 --> 27:30.162
♪ But like a drug that makes you blind ♪

27:30.187 --> 27:32.718
♪ It'll fool you every time ♪

27:32.743 --> 27:36.592
♪ The trouble with love is ♪

27:37.274 --> 27:41.233
♪ It'll tear you up inside ♪

27:41.258 --> 27:45.397
♪ Make your heart believe a lie ♪

27:45.422 --> 27:48.434
♪ It's stronger than your pride ♪

27:48.459 --> 27:51.627
♪ The trouble with love is ♪

27:52.847 --> 27:56.756
♪ It doesn't care how fast you fall ♪

27:56.781 --> 28:00.647
♪ And you can't refuse the call ♪

28:00.672 --> 28:07.436
♪ See, you've got no say at all ♪

28:07.871 --> 28:09.704
I just sang to you, didn't I?

28:10.382 --> 28:12.241
Woman, when I want to go to the store,

28:12.266 --> 28:14.520
- let me go to the store.
- What changed with Simon?

28:14.545 --> 28:17.106
Because this is a completely
different you than yesterday.

28:17.131 --> 28:18.799
I don't want to make
this any more confusing

28:18.823 --> 28:21.535
than it already is,
but he is not a player.

28:21.559 --> 28:24.938
He's tortured by this,
and love is messy.

28:24.962 --> 28:26.773
And if you ask me my honest opinion,

28:26.797 --> 28:32.155
I think he's a sweet,
sensitive, very confused guy.

28:33.792 --> 28:36.530
And this is the first time I
don't have any advice for you.

28:39.810 --> 28:42.156
What... what are you?

28:42.381 --> 28:44.036
Ugh, where does this go?

28:44.061 --> 28:46.256
Hey, so it's been almost a day.

28:46.281 --> 28:48.239
Are you... Are you talking to me yet?

28:48.264 --> 28:50.522
'Cause I don't really know what I did...

28:50.547 --> 28:52.024
- Well...
- ... exactly.

28:52.049 --> 28:54.094
You came home last night
when I was already asleep,

28:54.119 --> 28:57.737
sat down next to me in bed,
and said, "Wanna do it?"

28:57.858 --> 28:59.506
It was a bad choice of words.

28:59.530 --> 29:01.795
It's just that Zoey told me
that you were in the mood,

29:01.820 --> 29:03.476
- so I thought...
- Zoey told you?

29:03.501 --> 29:05.114
I'm glad it's clearer

29:05.139 --> 29:06.713
coming from your sister
than your own wife.

29:06.737 --> 29:08.415
Well, I guess I'm just not used to you

29:08.439 --> 29:09.856
being forward like that.

29:09.881 --> 29:13.270
David, do you have any idea
how long it's been?

29:13.295 --> 29:15.342
Two months, three weeks, and four days.

29:15.519 --> 29:18.024
Or something like that. I don't know.

29:18.049 --> 29:19.991
So what's the problem? Are you...

29:20.834 --> 29:23.662
Are you not attracted
to me anymore or...

29:23.687 --> 29:26.232
Are you out of your mind? No.

29:26.257 --> 29:28.835
The opposite of that.
I'm extremely attracted to you.

29:28.859 --> 29:30.737
It's just your body is going through

29:30.761 --> 29:32.906
all these changes right now,
and I don't know

29:32.930 --> 29:34.776
what's going on inside you,
what you're feeling.

29:34.800 --> 29:36.710
I-I'm trying to be respectful and...

29:36.734 --> 29:38.412
Just shut up, and have sex with me.

29:38.970 --> 29:42.067
You... you mean right now?
Because we could go upstairs

29:42.092 --> 29:43.450
and take my race car bed for a spin.

29:43.474 --> 29:45.085
Definitely not.

29:45.109 --> 29:48.497
I want to finish this
bassinet and then go home.

29:48.842 --> 29:50.390
Great plan. Love that plan.

29:50.415 --> 29:51.615
David...

29:52.740 --> 29:54.239
the bassinet.

29:55.235 --> 29:56.780
Yep, on it.

30:07.475 --> 30:09.264
Hey, you... two.

30:09.289 --> 30:11.311
Z-dawg, this girl is legit.

30:11.336 --> 30:13.217
We gotta get her an internship.

30:13.459 --> 30:15.505
Since when do you know sign language?

30:15.530 --> 30:18.278
Junior year of high school,
Tegan Schloss,

30:18.303 --> 30:20.754
dopest body in the land,
couldn't hear a lick.

30:20.778 --> 30:22.289
I taught myself to sign for her.

30:22.313 --> 30:24.758
Never sealed the deal,
but I did fall in love

30:24.782 --> 30:26.793
with the expressive
physical movements of ASL.

30:26.817 --> 30:29.311
You're a man of constant surprises.

30:30.154 --> 30:32.232
Thank you for inviting me here.

30:32.256 --> 30:34.459
I'm really excited about Sprq Point.

30:34.484 --> 30:36.462
Before we get into work stuff,

30:36.487 --> 30:40.444
we need to talk about your father.

30:41.122 --> 30:43.326
Whoa, you tricked me into coming here

30:43.351 --> 30:44.577
- to talk about my dad?
- Oh.

30:44.602 --> 30:45.746
- Not cool.
- No.

30:45.770 --> 30:48.123
- I added the "not cool" part.
- Right.

30:48.148 --> 30:52.228
Um, it's just that your father
means a lot to our family,

30:52.253 --> 30:56.231
and you seem really upset right now.

30:56.256 --> 30:58.489
Ever since I was little,
he's always tried

30:58.514 --> 31:01.361
to shelter me from the
world and make me better,

31:01.385 --> 31:02.929
whether it was cochlear implants

31:02.953 --> 31:05.032
or hearing aids or speech therapy,

31:05.056 --> 31:09.545
but when nothing fixed me,
he was devastated.

31:10.342 --> 31:12.944
Doesn't that show how
much he cares about you?

31:14.298 --> 31:17.778
Maybe to him, but he always made me feel

31:17.802 --> 31:19.616
like something was wrong with me.

31:19.641 --> 31:21.952
And then I went to
college and met people

31:21.977 --> 31:24.311
who didn't view their
deafness as a weakness.

31:26.069 --> 31:28.967
I now know I can do
anything I want to do.

31:32.059 --> 31:33.459
Like go to Kenya.

31:33.484 --> 31:35.303
Exactly.

31:35.767 --> 31:40.694
I could choose to wallow
or feel bad for myself,

31:40.719 --> 31:43.662
or I could embrace life, take control,

31:43.687 --> 31:45.364
and make my own destiny.

31:45.881 --> 31:49.698
I'm not gonna let him
or anyone else stop me.

31:52.997 --> 31:54.998
I'm not crying. You're crying.

31:56.248 --> 31:57.727
Hey.

31:58.405 --> 32:00.975
When I said I wanted to
discuss the kiss the other day,

32:01.000 --> 32:02.858
I never said how I was feeling,

32:02.883 --> 32:04.264
but...

32:05.141 --> 32:09.057
it's time, and I'm ready.

32:09.201 --> 32:11.920
Okay. I'm listening.

32:12.395 --> 32:16.876
Let me start off by
saying that I refuse,

32:16.901 --> 32:19.748
refuse to be a home wrecker,

32:19.773 --> 32:23.991
and I will never be the other woman.

32:24.648 --> 32:26.116
Nonetheless,

32:26.141 --> 32:29.998
I care about you, Simon, a lot.

32:30.482 --> 32:33.467
We have a chemistry and a
bond that is undeniable,

32:33.492 --> 32:36.506
and I guess I was hoping
that after the kiss,

32:36.531 --> 32:40.144
you'd have some clarity about all of it,

32:40.169 --> 32:45.561
clarity you still don't
have and maybe never will.

32:45.586 --> 32:50.522
So I have to make a change,
instead of just sitting around

32:50.547 --> 32:54.248
and waiting and hoping
for something to happen.

32:54.273 --> 32:57.405
So this is me saying to you...

32:58.311 --> 33:00.061
officially...

33:00.752 --> 33:06.506
I can't and I won't do this anymore.

33:18.818 --> 33:22.225
You did not have to get me those.

33:22.250 --> 33:24.256
I had to do something to thank you

33:24.281 --> 33:28.427
for helping David and I with our issues.

33:28.560 --> 33:32.094
Well, I'm hoping
that means they're resolved.

33:32.119 --> 33:35.753
Well, if I wasn't already
pregnant, I am now.

33:43.577 --> 33:45.558
Maggie, is everything okay?

33:46.676 --> 33:49.155
Yes. I'm sorry.

33:49.180 --> 33:51.128
I'm happy for you, truly.

33:51.153 --> 33:54.099
I just went down
memory lane for a second,

33:54.124 --> 33:57.222
which is never a good idea,
'cause that's not...

33:57.857 --> 33:59.653
where we're at.

34:01.543 --> 34:03.097
Hey, where's Howie?

34:03.122 --> 34:04.784
He's in the kitchen.

34:13.443 --> 34:15.675
- Can we talk?
- Depends.

34:16.103 --> 34:18.603
Are you gonna want half of
this fluffernutter or not?

34:18.629 --> 34:19.940
Oh, I definitely do.

34:19.965 --> 34:22.478
Then I definitely want to talk to you.

34:23.186 --> 34:27.058
So I invited Abigail
to Sprq Point today,

34:27.083 --> 34:29.984
and I think she has a real
chance at interning for us...

34:31.402 --> 34:33.589
after she gets back from Kenya.

34:34.148 --> 34:37.260
I thought I said that was a no-go.

34:37.284 --> 34:39.018
You did, but here's the thing.

34:39.043 --> 34:40.420
I somehow have found myself

34:40.445 --> 34:42.853
becoming more of a
caregiver like you lately,

34:42.879 --> 34:47.572
and it can be challenging
sometimes knowing

34:47.598 --> 34:53.339
the right way and the wrong
way to take care of somebody.

34:53.364 --> 34:56.714
Well, people aren't always
their own best advocates.

34:56.739 --> 34:58.534
But Abigail is.

34:58.784 --> 35:00.370
She knows what she wants.

35:00.395 --> 35:02.339
She's smart, capable.

35:02.364 --> 35:03.631
All due respect,

35:03.656 --> 35:06.768
you have no idea what it's
like to raise a deaf child.

35:06.793 --> 35:09.651
The world is a dangerous place, Zoey.

35:09.676 --> 35:10.902
That's true.

35:11.450 --> 35:15.214
But you also told me
that every day is a gift,

35:15.239 --> 35:18.058
and she's not a little girl anymore,

35:18.083 --> 35:22.118
so don't you think it's time
that she makes her own choices?

35:26.971 --> 35:28.618
Breathes her own breaths?

35:43.567 --> 35:44.766
Hey.

35:45.816 --> 35:47.933
I wanted to tell you something.

35:48.257 --> 35:50.589
I got offered a job on the sixth floor.

35:50.614 --> 35:53.378
- You applied for another job?
- No, no. I was...

35:53.809 --> 35:56.793
recruited, actually, by Ava Price.

35:56.818 --> 35:58.863
She wants me to manage her
whole engineering team.

35:58.888 --> 36:01.910
That's huge, Max. Congratulations.

36:01.935 --> 36:04.947
Thank you.
It's a pretty great opportunity.

36:05.218 --> 36:06.668
You think I should take it?

36:06.693 --> 36:10.738
As your boss, it'll be
very hard to lose you, but...

36:11.925 --> 36:14.692
as your friend, how could
I tell you not to take it?

36:15.502 --> 36:17.324
And what about the Zoey

36:17.349 --> 36:19.503
who sang "I'm Yours" to me?

36:21.857 --> 36:23.957
She's...

36:26.498 --> 36:29.499
gonna miss sitting across
from you every day.

36:31.248 --> 36:35.441
But... she'd never stop you from
going after what you want.

36:38.869 --> 36:40.746
Was that the right answer?

36:43.060 --> 36:44.457
No...

36:45.215 --> 36:46.882
but it just gave me mine.

36:55.715 --> 36:57.510
<i>Take it up, all the way.</i>

36:57.535 --> 36:58.794
- <i>And lift, and lift.</i>
- You know, I think

36:58.818 --> 37:00.616
I do actually feel the
endorphins kicking in.

37:00.641 --> 37:02.853
Uh-huh. So do I,

37:02.878 --> 37:05.556
and I don't think I like it,
but you seem better.

37:05.581 --> 37:06.746
Well, I was hanging out

37:06.771 --> 37:08.223
with this super-cool girl this morning,

37:08.247 --> 37:10.340
and you'd think her life
would be hard 'cause she's deaf,

37:10.364 --> 37:12.019
but she's got it, like, all figured out.

37:12.044 --> 37:15.464
And I'm the one sitting
there all down in the dumps

37:15.489 --> 37:17.464
because I occasionally sing

37:17.489 --> 37:19.855
or hear someone sing out loud?
What's up with that?

37:19.880 --> 37:21.910
Ever heard of the
term "white privilege"?

37:23.142 --> 37:25.287
Anyways, she totally motivated me

37:25.312 --> 37:27.113
to go to Simon and speak my truth,

37:27.138 --> 37:29.533
and I told him I am not

37:29.558 --> 37:32.018
going to get stuck
in this pattern anymore.

37:32.043 --> 37:33.321
And how'd he react to that?

37:33.346 --> 37:34.346
No idea.

37:35.320 --> 37:37.298
But honestly, I'm okay.

37:37.323 --> 37:39.668
I mean, I'm bummed,

37:39.693 --> 37:43.556
but maybe Simon was just a flirtation,

37:43.581 --> 37:46.174
you know, a special moment
in time for both of us.

37:46.199 --> 37:48.077
So does this mean you're not broken?

37:48.102 --> 37:51.205
Well, no, I'm definitely broken,

37:51.597 --> 37:53.954
but at least this is
starting to feel better.

37:53.979 --> 37:55.611
God, I'm tired.

37:56.354 --> 37:57.705
<i>And lift!</i>

37:57.730 --> 37:59.768
_

38:00.408 --> 38:01.409
You know, I always thought

38:01.433 --> 38:02.878
that I would look good
in one of these things,

38:02.902 --> 38:04.002
but I wasn't sure.

38:04.027 --> 38:06.455
I mean, I could... Oh, hey, Zoey.

38:06.480 --> 38:10.096
- What's all this?
- Emily bought us a chairlift.

38:10.121 --> 38:11.885
Now Mitch can move safely up the stairs

38:11.910 --> 38:13.072
without being carried.

38:13.097 --> 38:15.155
And we can sleep in
the same bed together

38:15.180 --> 38:16.323
like we used to.

38:16.347 --> 38:18.260
That is really amazing, Emily.

38:18.285 --> 38:21.133
It's more than amazing.
It's way too much.

38:21.158 --> 38:22.713
Hey, I did not sell my soul

38:22.738 --> 38:24.807
and go into corporate law for nothing.

38:24.832 --> 38:27.510
I did it so I can buy my
family extravagant gifts.

38:27.535 --> 38:29.057
And so that she can lord it over me

38:29.082 --> 38:30.760
that she's the main breadwinner.

38:30.785 --> 38:34.104
This thing is like the
Lamborghini of chairlifts, okay?

38:34.780 --> 38:36.290
In price, not in speed.

38:36.315 --> 38:38.268
I got a few more of these runs left

38:38.293 --> 38:39.832
before I'm outta here.

38:40.285 --> 38:43.893
What's wrong with just
using a regular flashlight?

38:47.045 --> 38:49.084
Yeah, I'm sure it would
be very cool, but...

38:49.109 --> 38:50.273
What's going on in here?

38:50.298 --> 38:52.276
We're just fighting over whether or not

38:52.301 --> 38:55.261
she should bring
infrared goggles to Africa.

38:55.286 --> 38:57.631
So I'm guessing Kenya's back on.

38:57.655 --> 38:58.933
Yes.

38:58.957 --> 39:01.101
I promised I would video chat with him

39:01.126 --> 39:02.711
over a cell phone once a week

39:02.736 --> 39:04.234
if it would make him feel better.

39:04.259 --> 39:05.679
Yeah, for the record,

39:05.704 --> 39:08.718
I told her that we could
do it every other week,

39:08.743 --> 39:11.648
but she could tell I was dying inside.

39:11.867 --> 39:13.445
It's that thrilling, right?

39:13.470 --> 39:14.805
All right. Yeah, right now...

39:14.829 --> 39:16.632
Of course I will miss you,

39:16.657 --> 39:20.257
but not enough to buy
you infrared goggles.

